name: Faunistic factors in the regeneration of mangroves of Gazi Bay and Mida Creek (Kenya)
description: In the first part of the dataset zonation of the mangrove vegetation is described, secondly, the predation of fauna (crab species) on the juveniles that were planted, and thirdly,explanations are searched using additional and preliminaryexperiment for the possible preferences of consumption of propagules. Experiments wereconducted from July to September 1993 in Gazi Bay and Mida Creek. The data weredigitized by VLIZfrom the original report: Verneirt, M. (1994). Faunistische factoren in de regeneratievan de Oostafrikaanse Mangrove: een casestudy in Gazi, Kenya = Faunisticfactors in the regeneration of East African mangroves: a case study in Gazi, Kenya. MScThesis. VUB: Brussels. 62 + references + bijlagen (30p) pp.
